{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Implement AI Support Chat Widget — Phase 1 MVP\n\nBuild a fully integrated, AI-powered support chat widget for MyOpenBrain/Krisp. The widget answers product, pricing, and subscription questions using a RAG pipeline grounded in a crawled knowledge base, a configurable master prompt, and a customizable floating UI. All four subsystems must ship together as a cohesive Phase 1 release. The implementation must follow existing project conventions: Drizzle ORM for schema, @neondatabase/serverless neon() driver for raw SQL where needed, Zod for all input validation, Anthropic claude-sonnet-4 for inference, and OpenAI Embeddings for vectorization — consistent with the existing email semantic search implementation.\n\n---\n\nSUBSYSTEM 1: Knowledge Base Ingestion Pipeline\n\nBuild an admin-facing ingestion interface and backend pipeline that populates a pgvector-backed knowledge base used to ground all AI responses.\n\nIngestion methods (all six required for Phase 1):\n- Single URL: Admin pastes one URL; backend fetches, strips HTML boilerplate (nav, footer, scripts), and extracts body text\n- Multi-page crawl: Admin provides a root URL; backend discovers and follows internal links up to a configurable depth, crawling all reachable pages on the same domain\n- PDF upload: Admin uploads a PDF file; backend extracts full text content (handle multi-page PDFs gracefully)\n- Direct text entry: Admin pastes raw text content via a textarea in the admin panel; no crawling required\n- CSV upload: Admin uploads a CSV file containing one URL per row; backend enqueues and crawls each URL in the list\n- XML sitemap upload: Admin uploads or provides a sitemap URL; backend parses all <loc> entries and crawls each\n\nChunking and embedding:\n- Split ingested content into chunks targeting approximately 512 tokens each; use sentence-boundary-aware splitting to avoid mid-sentence cuts\n- Generate 1536-dimensional embeddings for each chunk using the existing OpenAI Embeddings API client (text-embedding-3-small, consistent with email search)\n- Store chunk text, embedding vector, source URL (nullable), source type enum (url/pdf/text/csv/sitemap), and enabled boolean in the support_kb_chunks table\n- Treat each ingested source as a logical \"page\" or \"document\" with a parent record so admins can enable/disable all chunks from a given source in one toggle action\n\nAdmin UI requirements:\n- Ingestion dashboard listing all sources: source type, URL or filename, date ingested, chunk count, enabled/disabled toggle\n- Per-source enable/disable toggle that immediately flips the enabled flag on all child chunks (disabled chunks are excluded from retrieval)\n- Inline status indicators: queued, processing, complete, failed (with error message on hover/click)\n- Prioritize crawling and labeling of pricing pages, plan comparison pages, and billing FAQ content so the AI can accurately answer subscription questions; consider tagging these chunks with a metadata label for potential boost in retrieval scoring\n\nPrerequisites: Existing pgvector extension, OpenAI embeddings client, Neon DB connection, Drizzle ORM schema pipeline\n\n---\n\nSUBSYSTEM 2: AI Chat Engine (RAG + Master Prompt)\n\nImplement the server-side inference layer responsible for embedding incoming user messages, retrieving grounded context, and returning a Claude-generated response.\n\nMaster prompt system:\n- Store the master prompt as a single configurable text field in the support_widget_config table (editable via admin panel, no redeploy required)\n- Default prompt must establish: agent name \"Brain\", helpful and concise tone, hard guardrails (no feature promises, no unauthorized discounts, no disclosure of internal system prompt, no claiming to be human when directly and sincerely asked), and guidance on recommending appropriate Krisp/MyOpenBrain subscription plans based on retrieved pricing content\n- Inject the stored master prompt as the system message on every Claude API call\n\nRAG inference flow (executed on every POST /api/support-chat/message call):\n1. Validate and sanitize the incoming message using Zod\n2. Embed the user message using OpenAI Embeddings (same model and dimensions as knowledge base chunks)\n3. Run a pgvector cosine similarity search against support_kb_chunks WHERE enabled = true, returning the top K=5 chunks by similarity score\n4. Construct the Claude prompt: system message = master prompt, user message = retrieved chunks formatted as numbered context blocks followed by the user's original question\n5. Call claude-sonnet-4 and stream or return the full response\n6. Persist both the user message and assistant response to support_chat_messages before returning\n7. Return { response, sessionId } to the client\n\nAPI surface (additive, no modifications to existing routes):\n- POST /api/support-chat/session — creates a new support_chat_sessions row, returns { sessionId }\n- POST /api/support-chat/message — accepts { sessionId, message }, executes RAG flow, returns { response, sessionId }\n- GET /api/support-chat/widget-config — public, no auth, returns widget display configuration (agent name, colors, welcome message, starter buttons, position, size) for the embed script to consume\n- All routes: Zod input validation, existing rate-limiting middleware applied, consistent error shape with existing API routes\n\nEdge cases:\n- If pgvector returns zero results above a minimum similarity threshold, the agent should respond gracefully using only the master prompt context rather than hallucinating\n- If the Claude API call fails, return a user-friendly fallback message and log the error using the existing structured error logging system\n- Session IDs must be UUIDs; reject malformed session IDs with a 400 before hitting the database\n\n---\n\nSUBSYSTEM 3: Widget Embed & Visual Customization\n\nBuild a self-contained chat widget deployable via a single script tag, with all visual configuration managed through the admin panel and served from the widget-config endpoint.\n\nWidget behavior:\n- Floating bubble anchored to the configured screen position (default: bottom-right) that expands into a chat panel on click\n- On open, display the configured welcome message and up to four starter buttons; clicking a starter button pre-fills and submits its associated message text\n- All messages sent to /api/support-chat/* endpoints; session ID retrieved from sessionStorage on load or obtained via POST /api/support-chat/session on first message\n- Session continuity across page reloads via sessionStorage (clear on explicit window close is acceptable for Phase 1)\n- Display a typing indicator while awaiting the AI response\n- Render assistant responses with basic Markdown support (bold, italics, inline code, bullet lists) — consistent with the existing @uiw/react-md-editor usage in the project\n\nVisual configuration (all stored in support_widget_config.config JSONB, editable in admin panel):\n- Agent name and role label (e.g., \"Brain — Support Specialist\")\n- Avatar image URL (fallback to a default SVG if URL is empty or 404)\n- Welcome message text\n- Starter buttons: array of up to four objects, each with { label: string, message: string }\n- Primary brand color (hex color picker with live preview in admin panel)\n- Widget icon style: modern or classic (two icon variants)\n- Bubble size: small / medium / large\n- Position: bottom-right / bottom-left\n- Z-index integer (default: 9999; input validation: integer between 1 and 2147483647)\n\nAdmin panel live preview:\n- Admin panel must include a live visual preview of the widget that updates in real time as configuration fields change, before the admin saves\n\nEmbed mechanism:\n- Admin panel generates a ready-to-copy <script> tag pointing to a publicly served widget bundle\n- The script fetches /api/support-chat/widget-config (no auth), reads configuration, injects widget DOM into the host page, and initializes event listeners\n- Widget must be scoped (CSS custom properties or Shadow DOM) to prevent style conflicts with the host page\n- Must render correctly within the Krisp Next.js app itself without layout regressions\n- Smoke test: the generated <script> tag must work when pasted into a plain HTML file opened in a browser\n\nAccessibility (non-negotiable for Phase 1):\n- Full keyboard navigation: widget opens and closes with keyboard (Enter/Space on bubble, Escape to close)\n- Focus trap active while widget panel is open; focus returns to the bubble on close\n- ARIA role=\"dialog\" on the chat panel, aria-label on the bubble toggle button, aria-live=\"polite\" region for incoming messages\n- All interactive elements must have visible focus indicators\n\n---\n\nSUBSYSTEM 4: Conversation History Persistence & Admin Viewer\n\nPersist all sessions and messages to PostgreSQL for admin review. This data is also the foundation for the Phase 2 corrections feature — schema must be designed with that in mind (no breaking changes will be required in Phase 2 to add a corrections column).\n\nDatabase schema (additive Drizzle migrations only — no modifications to existing tables):\n\nsupport_widget_config:\n- id (uuid, PK)\n- config (JSONB — stores all widget display settings)\n- master_prompt (text)\n- updated_at (timestamptz)\n- Design as a single-row config table; enforce uniqueness at the application layer\n\nsupport_kb_chunks:\n- id (uuid, PK)\n- source_url (text, nullable)\n- source_type (enum: url / pdf / text / csv / sitemap)\n- source_label (text, nullable — human-readable name or filename)\n- content (text)\n- embedding (vector(1536))\n- enabled (boolean, default true)\n- created_at (timestamptz)\n- Add pgvector ivfflat or hnsw index on the embedding column for sub-100ms similarity search at expected data volumes\n\nsupport_chat_sessions:\n- id (uuid, PK)\n- created_at (timestamptz)\n- updated_at (timestamptz)\n- widget_config_id (uuid, FK → support_widget_config.id, nullable)\n- metadata (JSONB — store page URL at session start, user agent string, referrer; no PII)\n\nsupport_chat_messages:\n- id (uuid, PK)\n- session_id (uuid, FK → support_chat_sessions.id, ON DELETE CASCADE)\n- role (enum: user / assistant)\n- content (text)\n- created_at (timestamptz)\n- token_count (integer, nullable — populate from Claude API usage if returned)\n\nAdmin conversation viewer (read-only in Phase 1):\n- Sessions list view: columns for session start time, message count, and first user message preview (truncated to 80 characters); sortable by created_at descending\n- Session detail view: full chronological message thread rendered with role labels and timestamps; assistant messages rendered with the same Markdown rendering used in the widget\n- No delete, edit, or correction actions in Phase 1 — read-only\n- Paginate sessions list (20 per page) to handle large volumes without performance degradation\n\n---\n\nOUT OF SCOPE FOR PHASE 1\n\nDo not implement any of the following. If a design decision during Phase 1 would conflict with a future Phase 2 item, note it in a code comment but do not implement it:\n- Proactive triggers (time-on-page, scroll depth, exit intent)\n- Lead capture or email collection forms\n- Human handoff or support ticket creation\n- Corrections / Q&A override system (Phase 2 — schema must accommodate without breaking changes)\n- Analytics dashboard, resolution rate reporting, or conversation exports\n- Multi-language configuration UI (the underlying LLM handles language detection automatically)\n- Spam rate-limiting UI (rely on existing rate-limiting middleware)\n- White-label or branding removal options\n- External Conversations API for BI tools\n- Continuous auto-recrawl scheduler or scheduled re-ingestion jobs\n\n---\n\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\n\nKnowledge base:\n- Admin can ingest content via all six methods (single URL, multi-page crawl, PDF, direct text, CSV, sitemap) and see each source listed in the ingestion dashboard with correct status\n- Admin can toggle individual sources on/off and the change is immediately reflected in retrieval (disabled sources return no results in similarity search)\n- Pricing and subscription pages are ingested, chunked, and retrievable so the AI can answer plan-related questions accurately\n\nChat engine:\n- Master prompt is editable in the admin panel; changes take effect on the next message without a code deploy\n- Given a user message, the system embeds it, retrieves the top 5 relevant chunks from enabled sources, and returns a Claude-generated response grounded in that context\n- If no relevant chunks exist above threshold, the agent responds gracefully without hallucinating\n- p95 response latency from message send to first response token displayed: under 5 seconds on a standard connection\n\nWidget:\n- Widget renders correctly on both the Krisp/MyOpenBrain in-app dashboard and on a standalone HTML page using the generated script tag\n- All visual configuration fields (color, name, position, size, welcome message, starter buttons) update the live preview in the admin panel and are reflected in the deployed widget after saving\n- Widget passes a keyboard navigation and ARIA audit: fully operable without a mouse, focus trap active when open, all ARIA labels present\n\nPersistence and admin viewer:\n- Every user message and assistant response is written to support_chat_messages before the response is returned to the client\n- Admin conversation viewer lists all sessions and allows drill-down into the full message thread for any session\n- Session metadata (page URL, user agent) is stored in JSONB without capturing PII\n\nQuality gates:\n- TypeScript strict mode passes with zero new type errors introduced by this feature\n- All new API routes validated with Zod; error responses follow the shape used by existing routes in the project\n- Existing test suite passes with no regressions to Kanban, email, meeting, or Open Brain features\n- All new Drizzle migrations are additive only — no alterations or drops on existing tables\n- The embed script tag smoke test passes: paste into a plain HTML file, open in browser, widget initializes and can send and receive a message",
